), symbol °C









, which is by definition equal in magnitude to the unit kelvin. A difference or interval of temperature may be expressed in kelvin or in degrees Celsius, the numerical value of the temperature difference being the same in either case. However, the numerical value of a Celsius temperatureCelsius temperature expressed in degrees Celsius is related to the numerical value of the thermodynamic temperaturethermodynamic temperature expressed in kelvin by the relation

