Special care must be taken when expressing temperatures or temperature differences, respectively. A temperature difference of 1⁢K









 equals that of 1⁢°C









, but for an absolute temperature the difference of 273.15⁢K









 must be taken into account. The unit degree Celsiusdegree Celsius (°C









) is only coherent when expressing temperature differences. 
